description:
Ellen White would return to America and settle on the West Coast, near San Francisco, in a house that would be named Elmshaven. She lived here for almost a decade and a half, writing some of her major books within this home. She would also have a direct and blunt interaction with the then GC President, A. G. Daniels that would have a profound impact on him and his ministry!

To find out more information about Elmshaven, Ellen White and A.G. Daniells visit our website to read our extended article.
